<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 12301 requires that undocumented vessels that are propelled by machinery be issued an identification number by the proper issuing authority in the State in which the vessel is primarily operated.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf697107e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf697107f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2018—Subsec. (b). <ref href="/us/pl/115/282">Pub. L. 115–282</ref> substituted “may” for “shall” and inserted “of” after “barge”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1992—<ref href="/us/pl/102/587">Pub. L. 102–587</ref> designated existing provisions as subsec. (a) and added subsec. (b).</p>
</note>
